[SN]TITLE[SN]
Eskdalemuir Tibetan monastery struck by thieves

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police are investigating a number of thefts at the Samye Ling Tibetan Centre in Dumfries and Galloway.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
They took place at the south of Scotland monastery some time overnight between Sunday and Monday.
A canteen was broken into and a small amount of cash and confectionery taken, and an attempt was made to enter sheds.
A yellow Wacker Plate compactor worth Â£3,000, which was being used in works on the site, was also stolen. A vehicle would have been needed to remove it.
